overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking validation against a detailed specification. The agent
  meticulously analyzed the existing codebase, pinpointing several areas where
  the implementation fell short of the acceptance criteria. Following this
  review, the agent proceeded to implement the identified missing features. Key
  additions included a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete with critical
  safety warnings, and sophisticated detection logic for complex sleep disorders
  like Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA) and Insufficient Sleep
  Syndrome, each accompanied by tailored recommendations. The agent also
  integrated weighted scoring for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) and
  expanded the CSV export functionality to encompass all collected questionnaire
  data. Furthermore, new questions were introduced to screen for pain severity
  and chronic fatigue, alongside dedicated sections for medical and mental
  health history. These enhancements were consistently applied across the
  application's data models, validation schemas, user interface, and both
  web-based and PDF report generation, significantly enhancing the
  questionnaire's diagnostic capabilities and data utility.
